reviewText: This is a cartoon from the early 1970s Saturday Morning cartoons - if you are a fan of those good ol cartoon days then you will love this set - only four episodes per volume - better if they did a season or complete series set. At the rate of four episodes per "volume" it will be expensive to acquire the complete series although the overall quality of the package makes it a desirable collectable.

reviewText: I bought this DVD for my 7 year old son, who's a huge Scooby Doo fan. It had been 30+ years since I last saw an episode of Scooby's All Star Laff-A-Lympics, and I must say that when I saw the starting of the show, it seemed like yesterday when I last saw the wonderful cast of characters as a 7 year old in 1977. What makes this unusual idea for a cartoon work so well is the Really Rottens, who try to devise ways to win in a not so honest fashion, which is simply entertaining. I also like the unusual events that make up the laff-a-lympics, such as climbing the Eifel Tower, or throwing a boomerang. This series may need some getting used to, as it's not your usual mystery-solving; this series is about a cast of characters from Hanna-Barbera cartoons split into 3 teams who try to emerge as 'lympic' champions. The Rottens are the team to watch.........REALLY watch!!
